1. DETERMINER, QUANTIFIER, AND ADVERB USES

ADJECTIVE USES DETERMINER, QUANTIFIER, AND ADVERB USES little /ˈlɪtəl/ CET4 TEM4 

1. DET You use little to indicate that there is only a very small amount of something. You can use 'so,' 'too,' and 'very' in front of little . 微少的 

例： I had little money and little free time. 我没什么钱，也很少有空闲时间。 

例： I find that I need very little sleep these days. 我觉得我现在需要的睡眠很少。 

2. QUANT Little is also a quantifier. 一点 [QUANT 'of' def-n] 

例： Little of the existing housing is of good enough quality. 现有的住房中少有质量够好的。 

3. PRON Little is also a pronoun. 少量 

例： He ate little, and drank less. 他吃得不多，喝得更少。 

例： In general, employers do little to help the single working mother. 总的来说，雇主很少帮助那些工作的单身妈妈们。 

4. ADV Little means not very often or to only a small extent. 不多 [ADV with v] 

例： On their way back to Marseille they spoke very little. 在他们回马赛的路上，他们说话不多。 

5. DET A little of something is a small amount of it, but not very much. You can also say a very little . 一点儿 

例： Mrs. Caan needs a little help getting her groceries home. 凯恩夫人需要一点儿帮助才能把杂货弄回家。 

例： A little food would do us all some good. 吃一点儿东西会对我们大家都有些好处。 

6. PRON Little is also a pronoun. 一点儿 

例： They get paid for it. Not much. Just a little. 他们拿到工资了。不太多，就一点点。 

7. QUANT Little is also a quantifier. 一点 

例： Pour a little of the sauce over the chicken. 往鸡肉上倒一点调料。 

8. ADV If you do something a little , you do it for a short time. 一小会儿 [ADV after v] 

例： He walked a little by himself in the garden. 他在花园里独自散了会儿步。 

9. ADV A little or a little bit means to a small extent or degree. (程度上) 有点 

例： He complained a little of a nagging pain between his shoulder blades. 他抱怨说他的肩胛之间有点持续的疼痛。 

例： He was a little bit afraid of his father's reaction. 他有点害怕他父亲的反应。 ADJECTIVE USES little /ˈlɪtəl/ (littler,littlest) ADV 

1. ADJ Little things are small in size. Little is slightly more informal than . (尺寸) 小的 

例： We sat around a little table, eating and drinking wine. 我们围坐在一张小桌子旁吃饭、喝酒。 

2. ADJ You use little to indicate that someone or something is small, in a pleasant and attractive way. 小巧的 [ADJ n] 

例： She's got the nicest little house not far from the library. 她在离图书馆不远处有座最漂亮的小房子。 

例： ...a little old lady. …一位娇小的老太太。 

3. ADJ Your little sister or brother is younger than you are. 年纪小的 [ADJ n] 

例： Whenever Daniel's little sister was asked to do something she always had a naughty reply. 每次让丹尼尔的小妹妹做点事情，她总是有调皮的回应。 

4. ADJ A little distance, period of time, or event is short in length. (时间、距离、比赛) 短的 [ADJ n] 

例： Just go down the road a little way, turn left, and cross the bridge. 只沿着公路走一小段距离，向左转，然后跨过那座桥。 

例： Why don't we just wait a little while and see what happens. 我们何不就等一小会儿，看看发生什么事。 

5. ADJ A little sound or gesture is quick. (声音或动作) 迅速的 [ADJ n] 

例： I had a little laugh to myself. 我暗自笑了笑。 

6. ADJ You use little to indicate that something is not serious or important. 微小的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...irritating little habits. …恼人的小习惯。

